main event: Two objects were sighted in the sky over La Junta, Colorado on March 31, 1966.
interesting points: The objects were sighted traveling in opposite directions, two minutes apart.
One object was traveling south to north and weaving side to side, while the other was traveling northwest to southeast and weaving side to side.
Military and civilian air traffic was in the area during the sighting, and an ECHO satellite was also southeast bound at the time.
The objects were identified as a satellite (EGLO II) and an aircraft.
The sighting lasted for approximately one minute.
result: Identified as a satellite and an aircraft
